ALGORITHM
1.	Start
2.	Initialize DPTR = 4600
3.	Read the number of data (N) to be transferred from memory location 4600H and store it in R1 register 
4.	Increment DPTR
5.	Read the next number and store it in the accumulator
6.	Increment DPH (46xx to 47xx)
7.	Store the content of the accumulator to memory location (47xx)
8.	Decrement DPH (47xx to 46xx)
9.	Decrement the R1 register and if it is not equal to zero go to step 4 else go to step 10
10.	Stop

